  "abstract": "Weeds are one the major production hazards in the cultivation of Sorghum (Sorghum vulgare pers.). Weeds\r\ncompete efficiently for both nutrients and moisture which are the two main limiting factors in rainfed Sorgbum.  The major weed flora of sarghum vary from place to place, but weeds like Cyperus, Cynodon aad some annual grasses and broad leaved weeds seem to be common...",
